My meme

This meme encapsulates the average experience of a uni student. 

library(magick)


meme_image <- image_read("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/1/1f/WomanYellingAtACat_meme.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(1000)

woman_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                          height = 500,
                          color = '#000000')%>%
  image_annotate(text = 'assignments, projects, labs and quizzes',
                 color = '#FFFFFF',
                 size = 30,
                 font = 'Impact',
                 gravity = 'center')

cat_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                          height = 500,
                          color = '#000000')%>%
  image_annotate(text = 'me',
                 color = '#FFFFFF',
                 size = 50,
                 font = 'Impact',
                 gravity = 'center')

first_row <- c(woman_text, cat_text)%>%
  image_append()

#meme image should be the size of 2 blank images
meme <- c(first_row, meme_image)%>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

meme_final <- image_border(meme, "#9EEACC", "20x10")

image_write(meme_final, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This animated GIF is a sombering critique on society. (lmao) 

library(magick)

#here is a comment here :)
frame1 <- image_blank(color = "#9EEACC", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Help.", size = 100, gravity = "center")
  
frame2 <- image_blank(color = "#ABEAD1", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Help..", size = 80, gravity = "center")
  
frame3 <- image_blank(color = "#BBECD8", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Help...", size = 60, gravity = "center")
  
frame4 <- image_blank(color = "#C7EBDC", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Help....", size = 40, gravity = "center")
  
frame5 <- image_blank(color = "#D1EADF", width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Help.....", size = 20, gravity = "center")

frame6 <- image_read('https://w7.pngwing.com/pngs/308/404/png-transparent-explosion-cartoon-comics-bomb-explosions-creative-comic-book-photography-creative-artwork.png') %>%
  image_scale(500) 


frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6)

animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 2)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
